I"<p><em>Why I decided to start building a website</em></p>

<p>Sweaty palms, a light headache, a faint feeling of hope. I experienced all those feelings only a few days ago while I was waiting for my assignment marking. The result of my assignment, that I had worked on so much, would finally be revealed.</p>

<p>After repeatedly refreshing ladok the mark appeared. For a short moment my headache increased. I hoped that frantically clicking on my screen to refresh would change result. But the letter didn’t change, it remained a big fat U.</p>

<p>I had failed. My heart sank.</p>

<p>Within a moment I was in bed, curled in a foetal position. The first thing I did after reconsidering my future was callmy boyfriend while fake crying. He came over immediately. We did some brainstorming. These were the results:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Living in a conversion van</li>
  <li>Renovating a €1 house in Italy</li>
  <li>Actually opening a sheep farm in Ireland</li>
</ol>

<p>Of course that wouldn’t help to improve my current state of mind. Instead I looked for an alternative to my studies. Something that would enable me a ‘work to live’ balance. As opposed to the dusty career that my studies promised me.</p>

<p>Around that time my boyfriend was very much engaged with his own project. He was designing a <a href="https://mr-volta.github.io/">website</a> for a friend. I had already tried to understand HTML a few times, but my motivation lacked. Starting from scratch wasn’t something that I wanted to start with. Somehow I manged to get inspired this time.</p>

<p>Thanks to my boyfriend I discovered a <a href="http://jekyllthemes.org/">website</a> offering themes that I could start out with. This gave me the chance to learn while working within an existing framework.</p>

<p>I decided</p>
